snippet.description: Here's where you find the best of the best, our top digital cameras across the board.

snippet.title: Click & Grow Smart Farm
snippet.description: This modular smart garden from Click & Grow promises to bring expandable vegetable gardening to any indoor environment.

snippet.title: Dyson DC59 Animal
snippet.description: The DC59 is an elegant, customizable vacuum that performed well on a variety of flooring surfaces and with an array of debris types. If you're not looking for a budget-friendly model, you can count on the DC59 to make vacuuming as enjoyable as possible.

snippet.title: Dyson DC65 Animal Upright Vacuum
snippet.description: The DC41's design disappointed us, and the DC65's isn't any better. Despite the strong performance scores, this pricey Dyson is still difficult to recommend.

snippet.title: Dyson DC41 Animal Complete
snippet.description: You don't need to pay $649 to own a vacuum that cleans at this level, and if you are paying that much, you deserve a machine with a better design than this.

snippet.title: Dyson DC50 Animal
snippet.description: You can buy a better-performing vacuum for far less money, making the Dyson DC50 a poor value.

snippet.title: Google adopts Boston Dynamics' animal robots
snippet.description: Google builds its robot fleet with another acquisition, Sprint may make a bid for T-Mobile, and Amazon sells Kindle Fire tablets on a payment plan.

snippet.title: Inside Fujitsu's cloud-powered farm of the future
snippet.description: Japanese farms are smaller and often less sophisticated than those elsewhere in the world. Can a suite of sensors, services, and -- yes -- cow pedometers from Fujitsu help them compete on a global scale?

snippet.title: BenQ W1080ST
snippet.description: The BenQ W1080ST short-throw DLP projector offers very good performance and extra placement flexibility, but the long-throw W1070 is a better deal.
